{
  "texts": [
    "Spike bursting is a common phenomenon observed in biological neurons.",
    "We assume that the neurons received two types of inputs: one is the high-frequency input that drives isolated spike events and the other is the low-frequency input that regulates the burst probability.",
    "This mechanism is similar to multiplexing, a known function of the dendrite 29.",
    "In the illustration, we consider the illustration that DH-LIF neurons could generate bursting spikes while vanilla LIF neurons cannot.",
    "In the vanilla LIF neuron, there is only a soma memory unit without dendritic memory."
  ]
}